<body>

<h1>Real Account Tracking System</h1>

<p>
This document explains how to track the real <b>Donchian20 QLD &rarr; QQQ &rarr; Cash exit strategy</b>
without needing to read the backtest scripts.
</p>

<div class="note">
Main version to track: <b>Donchian20 QLD &rarr; QQQ &rarr; Cash exit strategy</b>.
The benchmark is <b>QQQ Hold</b>. The strategy can hold QLD, QQQ, or Cash.
There is no gradual DCA transition.
</div>

<h2>1. Purpose</h2>

<p>The tracking system should answer these questions after every trading day:</p>

<ol>
<li>Is the Donchian20 signal currently 1 or 0?</li>
<li>Should the account hold QLD, QQQ, or Cash?</li>
<li>Did today create a trade?</li>
<li>What are the real account shares, cash, and total value?</li>
<li>How is the account performing compared with QQQ Hold?</li>
<li>Are current and maximum drawdown still acceptable?</li>
</ol>

<h2>2. Required Market Data</h2>

<p>Use daily adjusted-close data for model calculations.</p>

<table>
<tr><th>Field</th><th>Use</th></tr>
<tr><td>QQQ adjusted close</td><td>Calculate QQQ EMA200 and value the QQQ position.</td></tr>
<tr><td>QLD adjusted close</td><td>Calculate the Donchian20 channel and value the QLD position.</td></tr>
<tr><td>QLD prior 20-day high</td><td>Creates a Donchian entry when QLD closes strictly above it.</td></tr>
<tr><td>QLD prior 20-day low</td><td>Creates a Donchian exit when QLD closes strictly below it.</td></tr>
<tr><td>QQQ EMA200</td><td>Determines whether the post-QLD-exit position remains in QQQ or moves to Cash.</td></tr>
</table>

<p>
The prior 20-day high and low exclude the current trading day. Use the most recent 20 completed
trading-day adjusted closes.
</p>

<h2>3. Strategy States</h2>

<table>
<tr><th>State</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>QLD</td>
<td>The Donchian20 signal is 1 and the account is fully invested in QLD.</td>
<td>Capture strong upward trends with 2x Nasdaq-100 exposure.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>QQQ</td>
<td>The Donchian20 signal has exited QLD, but QQQ is still at or above EMA200.</td>
<td>Reduce leverage from 2x to 1x without leaving a healthy long-term trend.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Cash</td>
<td>The account is outside QLD and QQQ is below EMA200.</td>
<td>Avoid holding QQQ during a weak long-term trend.</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h2>4. Donchian20 Signal</h2>

<h3>Signal Changes from 0 to 1</h3>

<p>
If the prior signal is 0, change the signal to 1 only when:
</p>

<ul>
<li>QLD adjusted close is strictly greater than QLD's prior 20-day high.</li>
</ul>

<p>
When the signal becomes 1, invest the entire strategy account in QLD at the model close.
This rule applies whether the prior account state was QQQ or Cash.
</p>

<h3>Signal Stays at 1</h3>

<p>
While the signal is 1, continue holding QLD until the exit condition occurs. A close that is
equal to the prior 20-day low does not trigger an exit.
</p>

<h3>Signal Changes from 1 to 0</h3>

<p>
If the prior signal is 1, change the signal to 0 only when:
</p>

<ul>
<li>QLD adjusted close is strictly less than QLD's prior 20-day low.</li>
</ul>

<p>
When the signal becomes 0, sell all QLD and initially convert the full account value to QQQ.
Then immediately apply the QQQ EMA200 exit layer described below.
</p>

<h2>5. QLD &rarr; QQQ &rarr; Cash Exit Layer</h2>

<table>
<tr><th>Current condition</th><th>Required model position</th><th>Action</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>Donchian20 signal = 1</td>
<td>QLD</td>
<td>Hold or buy QLD with 100% of the strategy value.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Donchian20 changes from 1 to 0 and QQQ is at or above EMA200</td>
<td>QQQ</td>
<td>Sell all QLD and buy QQQ.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Donchian20 changes from 1 to 0 and QQQ is below EMA200</td>
<td>Cash</td>
<td>Sell all QLD. The model passes through QQQ and exits to Cash on the same close.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Already holding QQQ and QQQ later closes below EMA200</td>
<td>Cash</td>
<td>Sell all QQQ and hold Cash.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Donchian20 signal remains 0 while in Cash</td>
<td>Cash</td>
<td>Remain in Cash, even if QQQ later moves above EMA200.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Donchian20 changes from 0 to 1 while in QQQ or Cash</td>
<td>QLD</td>
<td>Invest the entire account in QLD.</td>
</tr>
</table>

<div class="warning">
<b>Important:</b> QQQ moving back above EMA200 by itself is not a re-entry signal.
After the account reaches Cash, it remains in Cash until QLD produces a new Donchian20 breakout.
</div>

<h2>6. Daily Decision Order</h2>

<p>Apply the rules in this exact order after the market closes:</p>

<ol>
<li>Update QQQ and QLD adjusted closes.</li>
<li>Calculate QLD's prior 20-day high and prior 20-day low.</li>
<li>Update the stateful Donchian20 signal.</li>
<li>If the signal is 1 and the account is not in QLD, move the full account to QLD.</li>
<li>If the signal changes to 0 while holding QLD, move the full account from QLD to QQQ.</li>
<li>If the account is now in QQQ and QQQ adjusted close is below QQQ EMA200, move the full account to Cash.</li>
<li>Record the ending position, account value, trade reason, shares, and cash.</li>
</ol>

<h2>7. Trade Reasons</h2>

<table>
<tr><th>Model code</th><th>Plain-English meaning</th></tr>
<tr><td><code>toQLD</code></td><td>Donchian20 signal is 1; move the full account into QLD.</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>QLD-&gt;QQQ_on_Donchian_exit</code></td><td>QLD broke below its prior 20-day low; sell QLD and buy QQQ.</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>QQQ-&gt;Cash_below_EMA200</code></td><td>QQQ is below EMA200; sell QQQ and hold Cash.</td></tr>
<tr>
<td><code>QLD-&gt;QQQ_on_Donchian_exit; QQQ-&gt;Cash_below_EMA200</code></td>
<td>The Donchian exit and EMA200 exit occurred together; the final required position is Cash.</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h2>8. Real Account Workbook Structure</h2>

<table>
<tr><th>Tab</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Main columns</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>settings</td>
<td>Inputs defining the account and tracking assumptions.</td>
<td>Start date, starting value, account name, benchmark, fees/slippage, current mode.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>prices</td>
<td>Daily adjusted-close data and indicators.</td>
<td>Date, QQQ close, QLD close, QQQ EMA200, prior 20-day QLD high, prior 20-day QLD low.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>model_signal</td>
<td>Daily signal and target position.</td>
<td>Prior signal, current signal, model position, required action, trade reason, strategy value.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>real_account</td>
<td>Actual brokerage holdings and value.</td>
<td>QQQ shares, QLD shares, cash, market value, account value, actual position, model difference.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>trade_log</td>
<td>Permanent record of actual trades.</td>
<td>Date, buy/sell, symbol, shares, fill price, dollar amount, reason, entered by, notes.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>benchmark</td>
<td>QQQ Hold comparison from the same real-account start date.</td>
<td>Benchmark shares, benchmark value, benchmark return, strategy value, lead/lag.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>dashboard</td>
<td>One-page operational view.</td>
<td>Donchian signal, current position, required action, values, drawdown, latest trade reason.</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h2>9. Daily Real-Account Update</h2>

<ol>
<li>Update market data after the final adjusted-close data is available.</li>
<li>Confirm the prior 20-day QLD high and low exclude today's close.</li>
<li>Confirm the QQQ EMA200 value.</li>
<li>Run the decision order in Section 6.</li>
<li>If there is no transition, record <b>No action</b>.</li>
<li>If there is a transition, calculate the target shares using the full account value.</li>
<li>Confirm the signal and target allocation before placing a real trade.</li>
<li>Record actual fill prices, actual shares, fees, and remaining cash in the trade log.</li>
<li>Reconcile the brokerage value against the workbook.</li>
</ol>

<h2>10. How to Track Real Shares</h2>

<p>Use actual account data for the real account. Do not replace actual fills with model closes.</p>

<table>
<tr><th>Field</th><th>How to update</th></tr>
<tr><td>QQQ shares</td><td>Previous shares plus actual buys minus actual sells.</td></tr>
<tr><td>QLD shares</td><td>Previous shares plus actual buys minus actual sells.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Cash</td><td>Previous cash minus purchases plus sale proceeds, after fees.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Account value</td><td>QQQ shares &times; QQQ price + QLD shares &times; QLD price + Cash.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Model difference</td><td>Actual asset value minus the model's target asset value.</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>11. Benchmark Rules</h2>

<ul>
<li>The primary benchmark is QQQ Hold.</li>
<li>The benchmark starts on the same date as the real strategy account.</li>
<li>The benchmark starts with the same initial value.</li>
<li>The benchmark remains fully invested in QQQ.</li>
<li>Use adjusted-close data so distributions are included consistently.</li>
<li>Compare strategy and benchmark values daily.</li>
</ul>

<h2>12. Dashboard Metrics</h2>

<table>
<tr><th>Metric</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
<tr><td>Donchian20 signal</td><td>1 means QLD mode; 0 means the strategy is outside QLD.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Current model position</td><td>QLD, QQQ, or Cash.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Required action</td><td>No action, buy QLD, reduce QLD to QQQ, or sell QQQ to Cash.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Real account value</td><td>Actual value using brokerage holdings and current prices.</td></tr>
<tr><td>QQQ Hold value</td><td>Value of a same-date, same-dollar QQQ buy-and-hold account.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Strategy versus benchmark</td><td>Dollar and percentage lead or lag versus QQQ Hold.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Current drawdown</td><td>Decline from the strategy account's prior high.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Maximum drawdown</td><td>Worst peak-to-trough decline since tracking began.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Latest trade reason</td><td>Plain-English explanation of the most recent transition.</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>13. Historical Research Reference</h2>

<p>
The saved research snapshot covering June 21, 2006 through May 29, 2026 reported:
</p>

<table>
<tr><th>Metric</th><th>Donchian exit strategy</th><th>QQQ Hold</th></tr>
<tr><td>Starting value</td><td>$1,000</td><td>$1,000</td></tr>
<tr><td>Ending value</td><td>$55,874.66</td><td>$19,087.74</td></tr>
<tr><td>CAGR</td><td>22.36%</td><td>Not stored in the strategy summary</td></tr>
<tr><td>Maximum drawdown</td><td>-35.91%</td><td>-53.55%</td></tr>
</table>

<p>
These figures are historical backtest results, not guaranteed future results. Real performance will
differ because of trade timing, spreads, taxes, fees, slippage, and data revisions.
</p>

<h2>14. Weekly Review Checklist</h2>

<ul>
<li>Confirm all QQQ and QLD adjusted-close prices are current.</li>
<li>Confirm the Donchian20 signal agrees with the prior 20-day QLD channel.</li>
<li>Confirm QQQ EMA200 is current.</li>
<li>Confirm real shares and cash match the brokerage account.</li>
<li>Confirm every actual trade appears in the trade log.</li>
<li>Review current drawdown and strategy lead/lag versus QQQ Hold.</li>
<li>Document any manual override and its reason.</li>
</ul>

<h2>15. Monthly Review Checklist</h2>

<ul>
<li>Save the brokerage statement.</li>
<li>Reconcile ending account value and cash.</li>
<li>Review monthly return versus QQQ Hold.</li>
<li>Review maximum drawdown and recovery progress.</li>
<li>Check for missing prices or indicator discontinuities.</li>
<li>Do not change the strategy rules without creating and testing a separate version.</li>
</ul>

<h2>16. File References</h2>

<table>
<tr><th>File</th><th>Use</th></tr>
<tr><td>build_donchian20_qld_to_qqq_cash_exit.ps1</td><td>Implemented source of truth for the strategy transitions.</td></tr>
<tr><td>donchian20_qld_to_qqq_cash_exit_daily.csv</td><td>Daily model history, positions, values, and trade reasons.</td></tr>
<tr><td>donchian20_qld_to_qqq_cash_exit_summary.csv</td><td>Saved performance and drawdown summary.</td></tr>
<tr><td>QQQ_daily_raw_with_donchian20.xls</td><td>QQQ data, EMA200, and Donchian signal source.</td></tr>
<tr><td>QQQ_daily_raw_with_synthetic_qld_from_2000_corrected.xls</td><td>QLD adjusted-price history and corrected research series.</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>17. Important Operating Rules</h2>

<ul>
<li>Use adjusted closes for model signals and indicators.</li>
<li>Use actual fill prices for the real account.</li>
<li>Do not mix model account value with real brokerage value.</li>
<li>Apply strict comparisons: QLD must be above the prior high to enter and below the prior low to exit.</li>
<li>Do not buy QQQ merely because QQQ rises above EMA200 while the account is in Cash.</li>
<li>Do not add DCA, volatility, EMA50, or EMA200-deviation filters to this strategy.</li>
<li>Do not revise historical trade-log rows; add correction rows.</li>
<li>If a signal is unclear or market data is incomplete, do not trade until it is verified.</li>
</ul>

</body>
